product_name: IT CosmeticsBye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment
summary: SummaryIT Cosmetics Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment visibly reduces under-eye bags in 15 minutes! This smoothing treatment provides a temporary lift, tightening, and de-puffing effect that lasts all day. Safe for sensitive skin and wears comfortably under makeup.
details: DetailsBenefitsIt's your temporary eye lift in a tube!Daytime under eye treatment delivers a temporary depuffing, tightening and smoothing effect in just 15 minutes that lasts until you wash it off before bed.With its strong, flexible hold, Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment can be applied to bare skin or as the last step of your makeup routine.Adapts to facial movements for comfortable, all-day and long-lasting wear that won't crease or crack.Easily removes with an oil-based cleanser like Bye Bye Makeup Cleansing Balm.FeaturesVisibly de-puffs, tightens, and smooths under-eye bags in just 15 minutes.Temporary "eye lift" effect lasts all day until removed.Comfortable, flexible hold that moves with your face. Won't crease or crack.Can be worn alone or under makeup.Easy removal with an oil-based cleanser.Safe for sensitive skin, dermatologist and ophthalmologist-tested, fragrance-free.Research Results94% say it lasts all day**Based on a 4-week consumer study.**Based on a 1-week consumer study.Item 2609657How To UseHow to Apply IT On Bare Skin:Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment is designed to work when skin is completely dry, so allow 2-3 minutes for your eye cream to fully absorb before applying this product.A pea-size amount per eye can be applied to bare skin.With light pressure, use your fingertip to glide evenly from inner to outer eye corners 2-3 times - minimal blending is best.Use your fingertip to gently tap or "feather" the product outward at the edges of each eye.Relax your face and let it go to work. Don't squint or smile until the product is completely dry (about 15 minutes). Then you're good to go!How to Apply IT Over Makeup:Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment is designed to work over makeup when all products applied are fully dried down. You can use a tissue or blotting paper to remove excess oil if needed.A pea-size amount per eye can be applied on top of makeup. Please note: If wearing with concealer, foundation or powder, Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment needs to be the last product you apply on top in order to work most effectively.With light pressure, use your fingertip to glide evenly from inner to outer eye corners 2-3 times - minimal blending is best.Use your fingertip to gently tap or "feather" the product outward at the edges of each eye.Relax your face and let it go to work. Don't squint or smile until the product is completely dry (about 15 minutes). Then you're good to go!How to Remove IT:Do not sleep with product on eye area. Always remove with Bye Bye Makeup Cleansing Balm or your favorite waterproof makeup remover.Gently massage Bye Bye Makeup Cleansing Balm or waterproof makeup remover onto dry skin, focusing on the areas with product.Rinse well with warm water or wipe off with a face cloth and pat dry.IMPORTANT NOTE:Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Daytime Treatment should be applied and removed as directed. Contact with eyes should be avoided. The product should not remain on the skin overnight. Before bed, always remove the product with a waterproof makeup remover, such as Bye Bye Makeup Cleansing Balm. If irritation is experienced, stop use of the product. If irritation persists or is severe, seek medical attention.IngredientsIsododecane, Aqua / Water / Eau, Acrylates/Isobornyl Acrylate Copolymer, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Silica Silylate, Alcohol Denat., Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Dimethicone, Lauryl Peg-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Hydrogenated, Styrene/Butadiene Copolymer, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Acrylates Crosspolymer-2, Caprylyl Glycol, Peg/Ppg-18/18 Dimethicone, Magnesium Sulfate, Silica, Tocopherol, Tris-Bht Mesitylene.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.comments: This is a fantastic product! I've already recommended it to two of my friends and they both purchased it.

reviews.headline: Not For Me
reviews.comments: First time user of this product due to the recommendation of the consultant in the store. I plan on returning. It stung underneath my eyes and I didn't see much of a difference.

reviews.headline: I would not buy this product again.
reviews.comments: This product did not work for me at all.

reviews.headline: I was hopeful
reviews.comments: I LOVE LOVE LOVE IT Bye-Bye under eye concealer and was hopeful this would work to de-puff my eyes complementing my dark circle concealer. I have tried it alone, under my concealer, over my concealer waiting the recommended 15 minutes and I noticed zero difference. I was hopeful that both products from the same line would be the temporary solution I have been looking for. Nope! While I noticed a slight tightening, overall I didn't see visible results. Putting the concealer on was a disaster! Sure the dark circles were covered but it enhanced my bags and fine lines that didn't really tighten. I am jealous of all this product worked for but it is not for me.

reviews.headline: Don't waste your money!
reviews.comments: I thought I would try this product because I have always loved IT Cosmetics. However,  this did not do ANYTHING for me. A big thumbs down!

reviews.headline: Takes a few, look more rested.
reviews.comments: This takes about 20 min to kick in but it does do the job. Was disappointed with how it didn't mix well with concealer. I'll probably try a diff product next time for comparison sake.

reviews.headline: Yes and No
reviews.comments: The number one thing for me is that it is hard to remove. I love the tight feeling l get when it dries, but i struggle to remove it from under my eyes. Kinda feels like the struggle to remove it defeats the purpose of the product.

reviews.headline: byebye baggy eyes
reviews.comments: I have tried several under eye products to cover/reduce/mask my puffy, dark circles under my eyes, & this one checks all the boxes. I love that it goes on last, after moisturizer and concealer or foundation. I used my fingertips, a brush left strange marks.

reviews.headline: Not Good
reviews.comments: I put it over my makeup as directed. It looked very cakey and ruined the makeup. I tried several times and still could not get the promised result. I regret buying this.

reviews.headline: Not for me.
reviews.comments: Although this product lightened my undereye area, it was very flaky but then difficult to remove, made my eyes feel tired and itchy, and enhanced my crow's feet.

media.headline: Not impressed.
media.caption:
I received It Cosmetics, Bye Bye Under Eye Bags Rapid Bag Reducer for free in exchange for my honest review.
I am not as impressed as I hoped I would be. Don't get me wrong, it does depuff, tighten, and smooth the under eye skin. But I feel as if I had to use a lot of product to get that to happen. Then from having to apply so much, it left my skin feeling tacky and heavy for a very long time. I tried it on clean skin and on top of concealer. I had to use a lot both ways. I love It Cosmetics and I use many of their products. I am just not impressed with this one.

I recommend this product if you're looking for a treatment to fight against under-eye bags.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I really love the effectiveness of this product! The one thing I do warn people buying it for the first time: apply your usual serums and facial lotion, then apply this highly effective product, wait a full 10 tob15 minutes with a relaxed face to allow for the full effects, THEN apply your make up on top. You do NOT want to apply this cream on top of your makeup. Trust me. I use this cream at least 3 to 5 days a week, daily on busy weeks.

This cream is worth every penny if you have puffy bags under your eyes like I do. I use this even on my forehead creases and  the creases surrounding my mouth. Oh! And you ABSOLUTELY will need to wash this product off throughly at the end of your day! Buy the cleanser recommended on this site, if not you'll need to wash your face at least twice to remove this fully. Do NOT leave this on your face over night.
faceoff_positive.headline: Love this!

faceoff_negative.comments: I tried this product a few times, but each time it kinda burned. Within 2 hours it dried into a white itchy powder on my face.  I really wanted this product to work,  but unfortunately I don't think that it is helpful.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not for me
